  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to the Ebola Virus Disease Epidemic in the Nz&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project, in line with the Government&apos;s priorities within the framework of the National Response Plan, aims to contribute to the interruption of the chain of transmission of EVD in the Nz&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; region by directing the response towards the target areas presenting high risks linked to the dynamics of mobility. The response strategy will focus on the current epicenter and the surrounding health districts of the N&apos;Z&#xE9;r&#xE9;kor&#xE9; region and will ensure points of entry and health control points capacity improving around the epicente, active search for contacts and suspected cases along the axes of mobility and support to public health information and cross-border management of health emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
